In LocalFileService#getFile(), there are two calls:

boolean isVirtualParent = ArchiveHandlerManager.isVirtual(remoteParent);
boolean isArchiveParent = ArchiveHandlerManager.getInstance().isArchive(new File(remoteParent));

Those two methods do not expect remoteParent to be null.  But for any root directory (e.g., C:\), its remoteParent is null.

So we need to add null checking before the calls to those two methods.
